Declare a global visited array. Write a function dfs that takes a vertex u. Inside: mark u visited,process u,loop through neighbors of u,and recurse on unvisited neighbors.
This template works for nearly every DFS problem. You will modify what happens when you process a vertex,but the structure stays the same.

Here's the complete implementation:
